t: Praise*p ye the Lord.*s I will praise the Lord*s with my whole heart, in the assembly of the upright, and in the congregation.
The*p works of the Lord*s are great, sought out of all them that have pleasure therein.
His*p work is honourable and glorious: and his righteousness endureth for ever.
He*p hath made his wonderful works to be remembered: the Lord*s is gracious and full of compassion.
He*p hath given meat unto them that fear him: he will ever be mindful of his covenant.
He*p hath shewed his people the power of his works, that he may give them the heritage of the heathen.
The*p works of his hands are verity and judgment; all his commandments are sure.
They*p stand fast for ever and ever, and are done in truth and uprightness.
He*p sent redemption unto his people: he hath commanded his covenant for ever: holy and reverend is his name.
The*p fear of the Lord*s is the beginning of wisdom: a good understanding have all they that do his commandments: his praise endureth for ever.
